1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,126
Dekho, samjho yeh carefully,  this is session 1 of our Apache Kafka series.

2
00:00:05,076 --> 00:00:09,778
Today's topic: Kafka Architecture — Brokers, Topics, Partitions, Offsets.

3
00:00:09,778 --> 00:00:14,355
Dekho, samjho yeh carefully,  chalo, pehle kuch facts sunte hain.

4
00:00:14,355 --> 00:00:18,701
Fact number 1: Kafka is just a message queue, like RabbitMQ.

5
00:00:18,701 --> 00:00:23,413
Fact number 2: Kafka guarantees exactly-once delivery out of the box.

6
00:00:23,413 --> 00:00:27,826
Fact number 3: More partitions always means better performance.

7
00:00:27,826 --> 00:00:29,000
Sab suna?

8
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,009
Accha.

9
00:00:30,009 --> 00:00:32,711
Ab dhyan se suno,  YEH SAB GALAT HAI.

10
00:00:32,711 --> 00:00:33,971
Haan, galat.

11
00:00:33,971 --> 00:00:36,682
Aur main tumhe exactly bataunga ki kyun.

12
00:00:36,682 --> 00:00:38,884
Kafka is NOT a message queue.

13
00:00:38,884 --> 00:00:41,028
It's a distributed commit log.

14
00:00:41,028 --> 00:00:45,721
Exactly-once requires idempotent producers AND transactional consumers.

15
00:00:45,721 --> 00:00:49,086
And too many partitions , actually HURT performance.

16
00:00:49,086 --> 00:00:51,221
Let me explain each one.

